1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,280
My friend's a fertility doctor.

2
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,840
We've got an appointment now.

3
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:11,440
I've made up my mind.

4
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,040
I'll tell Pun about my miscarriage.

5
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:16,240
Are you crazy?! Why would you tell him?

6
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,760
It's the truth, Mom.

7
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:20,760
Have you thought about how I'll be?

8
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,600
Since you got married,
have you been happy?

9
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,560
Pun.

10
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:30,200
It's because you're like this
that we still don't have any children.

11
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,960
If you don't stop causing trouble,

12
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:36,720
I'll reveal the truth
and end all these problems.

13
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,440
Pie, how are you?

14
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,560
Did the medicine I gave you work?

15
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:49,880
Yes, Mom. It still hasn't stopped.

16
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,280
I'm tired.

17
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,240
<i>Hang in there.</i>

18
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:58,120
At least you won't discuss
the miscarriage with the doctor.

19
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:04,520
Now, you need to get pregnant soon,
so you won't need to see the doctor again.

20
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:09,800
Okay, Mom. I'll talk to you later.

21
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:37,160
<i>Secrets in love can be the cause</i>
<i>of a relationship falling apart.</i>

22
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:46,560
<i>Once you start lying,</i>
<i>you have to keep lying.</i>

23
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:48,760
<i>But if we tell the truth,</i>

24
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,560
<i>and it makes the other person</i>
<i>uncomfortable or upset,</i>

25
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,040
<i>is it really okay?</i>

26
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,000
I SAY IT LIKE THIS

27
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:57,680
<i>Telling the truth requires skill.</i>

28
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:03,640
<i>I understand, sometimes we lie</i>
<i>to protect the people we love.</i>

29
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,960
<i>Some people lie to make</i>
<i>the other person feel better.</i>

30
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:14,160
<i>Some lie to get what they want.</i>

31
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,720
Hey, Bee.

32
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,800
I'm really sorry,
but we need to reschedule today.

33
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,600
Pie's having really bad diarrhea.

34
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,960
Thanks for understanding. Sorry again.

35
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:30,520
<i>But honestly, in any relationship,</i>

36
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:34,040
<i>no one wants to be lied to repeatedly,</i>

37
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:37,160
<i>and no one likes to keep lying either.</i>

38
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:42,320
<i>If I don't want to keep lying,</i>
<i>what should I do?</i>

39
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,480
<i>I say it like this.</i>

40
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:48,160
<i>You need to use sincerity</i>
<i>and a bit of tact.</i>

41
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,680
<i>Find the right moment to tell the truth.</i>

42
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,240
<i>But most importantly,</i>

43
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:56,080
<i>be ready to face the consequences</i>
<i>of the truth being revealed.</i>

44
00:04:56,880 --> 00:05:00,960
<i>Whether it's heavy or light</i>
<i>depends on how much you've lied.</i>

45
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,480
<i>I'm here to support you.</i>

46
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,600
I SAY IT LIKE THIS

47
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,480
Hey.

48
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,320
How are you feeling? Is it better now?

49
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,480
I already talked to Dr. Bee.

50
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,000
I apologized to her.

51
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:45,160
She said she'd find a new appointment
for us, probably soon.

52
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,560
Pie.

53
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,800
Is something wrong with you?

54
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:03,120
Or is it that you actually
don't want to have kids?

55
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,480
No.

56
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,880
I'm just tired.

57
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:13,840
There's a lot to think about,
so I'm stressed.

58
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,280
Pie.

59
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,800
I need to ask you honestly.

60
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:30,120
Since we got married,

61
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,000
have you been happy with me,

62
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,040
living together?

63
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,320
Why…

64
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,920
Why are you asking me this?

65
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,600
I just feel like the longer
we're together,

66
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,160
the more you've changed.

67
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,440
You're not the same Pie I met.

68
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,640
Pie, who was full of life,
seems to be fading away.

69
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:28,240
I don't want you to turn
into a housewife who's lost her spark.

70
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,040
That's why I'm asking

71
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,880
if you're truly happy.

72
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:44,560
If I'm not doing my job
as a husband right,

73
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:48,480
you need to tell me.

74
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,040
- It's just that--
- Hold on.

75
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,200
MUNGMINK

76
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,760
Sorry.

77
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,320
I just remembered I have a meeting
with Mink about the design.

78
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,440
I sent her the work.

79
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,040
Let me quickly take care of that.

80
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,040
Okay.

81
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,840
Hello, Mink?

82
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:27,200
<i>I might have a head injury,</i>
<i>but my memory's fine.</i>

83
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,280
<i>I remember we scheduled to meet tonight.</i>

84
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,280
Good to hear your memory's fine.

85
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,200
I sent the design over. Have you seen it?

86
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,200
What do you think?

87
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,400
Puk, you traitor!

88
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:53,560
How could you betray me like this?

89
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,920
I'm sorry, ma'am.

90
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,520
I didn't betray you.
I just lost my motivation.

91
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,720
Lost your motivation, my foot!

92
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,000
I've been kind,
taking care of you so well,

93
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,640
and this is how you repay me?

94
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,880
- Mom!
- Ma'am!

95
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,840
Mom, stop!

96
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:11,280
What's going on?

97
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:14,520
Just look at Puk! She's going to quit
and work for a new boss.

98
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,200
Miss Pie.

99
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,000
I'm bored with Bangkok.

100
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,960
I got a new job in Ratchaburi.

101
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:26,080
My new boss just had a baby,

102
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,480
and she needs someone
to help with housework.

103
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:33,280
Word got around, and I agreed.

104
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:38,600
It's all the same here. I'm bored.

105
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,240
I'm burned out.

106
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,360
I want to add some excitement to my life.

107
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,560
- Hey, stop right there!
- Mom!

108
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,640
- Mom!
- Ma'am!

109
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,320
- You sound like my ex-husband!
- Mom!

110
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:53,360
- That's too much!
- Mom, calm down.

111
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,280
Mom!

112
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:59,080
Puk has found something
she wants to do. Let her go.

113
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,840
Mom, please.

114
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,200
Please, ma'am.

115
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,120
Please, ma'am.

116
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,720
Please, ma'am.

117
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,040
Please let me go.

118
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,440
Fine!

119
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,160
You really want to go, don't you?

120
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:25,800
If you really want to go, then go.

121
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:31,680
Ma'am, thank you so much.

122
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:34,160
You've worked with me for a long time.

123
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:40,200
On your last day,
I'll take you to Ratchaburi myself.

124
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:48,200
Ma'am, I'm so lucky to have known you.

125
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,280
You're such a good person.

126
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:55,360
I'll remember your kindness forever.

127
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,040
Thank you, ma'am.

128
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,520
How's your stomach?

129
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,160
Is it feeling better, Pie?

130
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:17,520
Mom, Pun will schedule
another doctor's appointment soon.

131
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:21,400
- When?
- I don't know, but it'll be soon.

132
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:24,880
Mom.

133
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,480
I won't hide or lie to Pun anymore.

134
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:28,600
Whatever happens, happens.

135
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,000
- Pie, but I think--
- Mom!

136
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,400
I've made my decision.

137
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,880
I'm ready to face the truth,
no matter what.

138
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,680
Pie, let me ask you honestly.

139
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:43,800
Are you this stubborn
because Win came back?

140
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:49,560
What has he said to you
that made you act this way with me?

141
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:51,200
What did he say to you?

142
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,640
Mom.

143
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:55,480
If you're going to talk nonsense
like this, I am leaving.

144
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,720
I came home to see you
and find peace of mind.

145
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:01,840
But if being here
only brings me stress, then I'll go.

146
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,840
Pie, wait a minute.

147
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:08,000
Sit down first. Please don't leave yet.

148
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,720
I won't say anything more.

149
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,920
I'm sorry.

150
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,800
The reason I asked
is because I'm concerned.

151
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:20,840
But if you realize it
and stay away from him, I'll be at peace.

152
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,720
Pie.

153
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:28,280
He already destroyed your life once.

154
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:31,720
I don't want him to do it again,
for the second time.

155
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:36,960
And this time, it won't just affect you.

156
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,800
It'll hurt Pun too.

157
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,920
The further you stay away from him,

158
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,360
the better, my dear.

159
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:49,680
You know, right?

160
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:08,160
I'll try to adjust the design
using the ideas that you and Mr. Dech

161
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,120
gave to Pun yesterday.
I'll update you again.

162
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,600
Okay.

163
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,280
That's all for now.

164
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,320
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

165
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,440
Okay.

166
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:19,240
I'll report to the boss first.

167
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:20,640
I need to go find him at the site.

168
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,520
Hey, Mink.

169
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:28,040
You've cleared up
Win's gender identity issue, right?

170
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,920
He's not secretly hooking up with Pun.

171
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,520
Did you think that too?

172
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,360
I saw it myself.
You two were all over each other.

173
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,680
All over each other?

174
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,280
Was it the day you brought me the book?

175
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,400
That's not it.

176
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:51,720
I made Pad Kra Pao,
and the chili got in my eye.

177
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:54,160
So, I had to rinse it out.
After rinsing, my shirt got dirty.

178
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,840
That's how we ended up looking like that.

179
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:59,400
I was messing with Pun,
and he messed with me right back.

180
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:01,080
We've been doing this since we were kids.

181
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:02,360
There's nothing to it.

182
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,000
How would I know?

183
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,240
I thought you two were sneaking around.

184
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,920
You're crazy.

185
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,600
I like women.

186
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,400
Why are you smiling ?

187
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:21,520
Nothing. I wasn't smiling.

188
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,920
I'm leaving now. See you later. Bye.

189
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,200
I'll go now.

190
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,840
Wait, Win.

191
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,400
Are you free after work?

192
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:57,400
I'm planning to go home
and do some more work.

193
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:00,880
It's after work. Take a break.
Let's go for dinner.

194
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:08,040
I know everyone here except for you, Win.

195
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:10,000
I want to get to know you better
to work more easily.

196
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:14,160
And the quickest way to get closer
is to grab a drink.

197
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,200
What about me?

198
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:18,640
You still need to work with Pun, right?

199
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:20,200
Not sure when you'll finish.

200
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:22,920
We can set something up later
when you're free.

201
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,600
Today, I want to get to know Win first.

202
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:27,760
What do you say?

203
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:39,560
Hey, Mink invited Win to dinner.

204
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,880
Do you think she likes him?

205
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:45,080
She knows I like Win, though.

206
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,000
<i>If I didn't have to meet Pun,</i>

207
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,320
I wouldn't let him go with her alone.

208
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,200
Rok, I'm asking seriously.

209
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,560
Do you really like Win?

210
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,600
Win's nice.

211
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:00,280
He's warm, like a microwave.

212
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:06,680
Rok.

213
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,040
Do you really know him well?

214
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,080
He might not be as nice as you think.

215
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:16,240
Pie, when did you start acting like this?

216
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:18,280
You never talk bad about anyone.

217
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:20,800
<i>Even with friends</i>
<i>who have terrible personalities,</i>

218
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:21,800
<i>you don't hold a grudge.</i>

219
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:25,120
And now, you're suspicious of Win?

220
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,840
I'm just worried about you.

221
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,760
Then why do you think he isn't nice?

222
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,320
What do you know?

223
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:38,640
No.

224
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:41,160
I just think…

225
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:47,800
I think you should get to know him better
before deciding to fall for him.

226
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:50,320
I don't want you to regret it later.

227
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:54,040
As for Mink,
whatever she does is her business.

228
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,600
Just don't jump to conclusions.
It might not be anything.

229
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:59,000
Okay, I won't overthink it.

230
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:03,520
That's it for now.
I have to rush to meet Pun.

231
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,680
Talk later. Bye.

232
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,840
<i>How did you get to know Pun?</i>

233
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,960
How many times have you asked?

234
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:38,880
I already told you, he was my neighbor.

235
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,320
Are you guys really close?

236
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:44,800
Closer than you.

237
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,400
Then you must know a lot about him.

238
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,760
What was he like as a kid?

239
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:52,960
Was he serious?

240
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:55,000
Or was he a nerd?

241
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,120
He must've been popular.

242
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,480
Did he have girls around him?

243
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:06,520
Do you realize that since we've sat down,

244
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:09,200
you've mentioned Pun's name
over a hundred times?

245
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,920
Really? Over a hundred?

246
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:20,920
Honestly,

247
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,320
do you want to get to know me,
or do you want to know about Pun?

248
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,600
Pun's a really nice guy.

249
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:32,480
If I want to get to know him,
there's nothing wrong with that.

250
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:36,320
But he's already married.

251
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,160
I know.

252
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:42,400
His wife is my friend, from university.

253
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,920
So why do you want to know
about your friend's husband?

254
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,920
I've wanted to know
even before he became her husband.

255
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,480
I've always been curious.

256
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,160
So, what's the big deal?

257
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:56,320
Just answer me.

258
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:01,920
I think,

259
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,360
if you want to know more about Pun,
you should just call him yourself.

260
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:07,040
As for me,

261
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:12,040
I don't like getting involved
in other people's relationships.

262
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,440
I'll go now.

263
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:20,680
Hey, wait! We're not done yet.

264
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,480
Mink.

265
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:30,920
Mink.

266
00:19:37,520 --> 00:19:39,760
- Here we go again.
- Hello, Uncle.

267
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:40,760
Hello.

268
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:43,120
Mink's been drinking a little too much.

269
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:46,760
Well, you're sweet. You know
how to make me feel better.

270
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:49,240
But in this state,
it's really far too much.

271
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,400
Seriously, look at this.

272
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:54,640
Alright.

273
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:57,960
Thanks for not leaving
this drunk girl by the roadside.

274
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,600
- No problem. Here.
- Go home.

275
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,080
- Here's her bag.
- Yeah, thanks.

276
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,480
- Goodbye, Uncle.
- Goodbye.

277
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:05,560
- Goodbye. Drive safely, okay?
- We will.

278
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:21,680
I'll drive you home. Get in the car.

279
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,840
What's wrong with my car?

280
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:11,080
Hey, hey.

281
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:14,640
Why did you call me
to help take Mink home?

282
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:19,840
I thought it would be better
if a female friend helped take Mink home.

283
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:22,800
She was completely passed out.
If it was just me,

284
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:24,160
it could cause a problem.

285
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,720
People might think badly of her.

286
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:29,000
Such a gentleman.

287
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,800
Isn't that a bit too much?

288
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:38,600
A gentleman like this
must never have made a woman sad.

289
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:51,320
Hey, Win, do you remember
what we talked about that day?

290
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:55,080
I still wonder why you've never
been serious with anyone.

291
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,360
Well…

292
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:00,920
I'm not good enough
to be serious with anyone yet.

293
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:05,000
Hey, is this how guys think?

294
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,960
My exes weren't any good.

295
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:12,120
Or they weren't serious with me
when we were together?

296
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:14,920
That's why it didn't work out.

297
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:16,880
The right person

298
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,320
comes at the right time.

299
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:23,640
Wait a minute. That's what Pek said!

300
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,680
- Right?
- Yeah.

301
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:29,240
I heard it from Pek.

302
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:35,160
The right person at the right time,
it's just perfect.

303
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,480
But if it's the wrong time,

304
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,760
then everything just goes wrong.

305
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:58,840
Aren't you eating?

306
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:02,200
I am. I was about to eat.

307
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,880
- Oh.
- Hello.

308
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:24,760
You're going to practice
meditation now, Sil?

309
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:26,280
- Yes.
- Wow.

310
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:27,960
I wish you good merit.

311
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:29,160
Thank you.

312
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:31,480
Look at you. You haven't
even stepped out the door,

313
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:32,760
and you're already radiating happiness.

314
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:36,240
When you're doing something good,
you naturally feel happy.

315
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:41,080
Try doing some good at home
with your family,

316
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,600
not just outside.

317
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:46,280
Seriously, you should spend
more time at home.

318
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:50,040
Come on. I'll be back soon.

319
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:52,240
This time, I'll stay home
and make you bored.

320
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:56,200
And for this trip, I'll also be silent.

321
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:57,800
No phone. Can't be contacted.

322
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,880
Again?

323
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:01,200
You're going too far.

324
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:03,000
You can stay silent at home.

325
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:08,320
With that kind of talk,
how is he going to stay quiet? Come on.

326
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:11,120
Hey, whose friend are you exactly?

327
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,680
Your friend, of course.

328
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:15,840
If your husband
wants to do good, let him be.

329
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,280
Your friend is right. Just let me go.

330
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:20,680
Okay?

331
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:24,200
I'm leaving now. See you later.

332
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:28,840
So eager.

333
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,760
Hey, Nhun.

334
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:33,800
Stop bothering him.

335
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,120
Let him go to the temple.

336
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:39,520
Better than being around college girls
and spending money on them.

337
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:42,280
- Do you want that?
- You talk too much.

338
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:47,720
I'll drive myself. Put it in my car.

339
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:48,840
Yes, sir.

340
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:09,720
We're on the right road.

341
00:25:10,520 --> 00:25:12,120
- Take the next left.
- Here?

342
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,040
- Next turn.
- Here?

343
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,640
Oh no, ma'am!

344
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:17,480
- What?
- Wrong alley. It's the one ahead.

345
00:25:17,560 --> 00:25:18,560
Oh, not this alley?

346
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:19,760
Let me back up and try again.

347
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,400
No worries, ma'am.

348
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,960
I'll walk from here.

349
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:25,160
Thank you for dropping me off.

350
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:27,120
Hey, Puk.

351
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:29,720
Maybe think it over again?

352
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:30,920
Ma'am.

353
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:33,560
I've already promised my new boss.

354
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:36,240
My boss is here. Over there.

355
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:51,760
Hey!

356
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:53,320
That's Mr. Sil!

357
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:57,000
The little one came to pick up Dad.

358
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:59,040
I missed you so much.

359
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:00,040
Come here.

360
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,280
- Puk.
- Yes?

361
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:11,600
You said

362
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:15,200
your new boss just had a baby, right?

363
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:21,440
That woman is my new boss,
and that's the baby.

364
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:24,240
So,

365
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,000
that means Mr. Sil…

366
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:30,520
He's the father of the child?

367
00:26:32,280 --> 00:26:35,240
Oh my, this is big news, Puk!

368
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:39,640
Hey, are you sure
you'll be able to work with him?

369
00:26:40,360 --> 00:26:41,400
He won't remember me.

370
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,400
You won't get away with this.

371
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:46,040
You'd better come back and work with me.

372
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:52,720
Why is this happening to me?

373
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,960
Dad bought a lot of stuff for you.

374
00:26:57,560 --> 00:27:00,080
Do you think Pun and his mom
know about this?

375
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:05,040
If they knew, the family would fall apart.

376
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:06,960
His mom is no joke at all.

377
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,520
I don't think she knows.

378
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,120
You're right about that.

379
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,720
Actually, it feels kind of satisfying.

380
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:18,120
Acting all high and mighty,
always putting others down,

381
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:20,720
but they're not any better
than anyone else.

382
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:27,040
Well, maybe catching them like this

383
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:30,200
could turn out
to be a good thing after all.

384
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,760
Come in.

385
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:01,240
Yes.

386
00:28:11,080 --> 00:28:12,120
Well.

387
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:14,520
You're just standing there in shock.

388
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,000
Never seen this before, huh?

389
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,600
Pull yourself together and sit down.

390
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,280
Do you like this jewelry?

391
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:37,000
I do. It's so beautiful.

392
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,920
The craftsmanship is so detailed.

393
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:40,280
You're observant.

394
00:28:41,280 --> 00:28:44,320
But just so you know,
I'm not giving it to you.

395
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:45,640
Don't get too excited.

396
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:51,240
By the way, did Pun tell you

397
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,960
about James Jewelry contacting you two

398
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:56,520
to do a photo shoot
for their 50th anniversary?

399
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:58,240
Yes, he did.

400
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,280
My family

401
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:05,400
has been a regular customer
since his father's time.

402
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:08,120
We've been supporting them continuously.

403
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:11,560
That's why he wants us to showcase
the jewelry made during his father's time

404
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:13,040
for a fashion shoot.

405
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,200
So, I was thinking of having you
wear this piece.

406
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:21,600
Thank you.

407
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:23,680
Why are you bowing?

408
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:27,880
I already said I'm not giving it to you.
No need to bow.

409
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:49,120
Can you tell the difference
between real diamonds

410
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,280
and fake ones?

411
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,920
I don't know.

412
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:57,160
Real diamonds are strong

413
00:29:57,760 --> 00:29:59,560
and not easily destroyed.

414
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:03,960
But synthetic diamonds are fake.

415
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:06,920
They break and degrade quickly.

416
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,600
People are the same way.

417
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:12,160
If they're not real, not genuine,

418
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,000
they'll eventually fall apart

419
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:17,320
and reveal their true nature.

420
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:23,280
Then people will see
they're just stones, not real diamonds.

421
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:34,640
Pun.

422
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:37,240
Can I skip the photoshoot?

423
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:39,480
No, Pie.

424
00:30:39,560 --> 00:30:42,640
I already promised my mom,
and she confirmed it with them.

425
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:45,960
But I really don't want to go, Pun.

426
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,120
Pie.

427
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:53,080
Honestly, I don't want
to upset you either.

428
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:56,360
But this time, I really want you to come.

429
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:59,440
We haven't done any events
together for a while.

430
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,960
I just want to show off my wife.

431
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:04,600
Please.

432
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:07,560
It's just a quick photoshoot.

433
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:08,520
Okay?

434
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:11,200
Don't overthink it.

435
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,120
Okay?

436
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,560
Sil has gone to a spiritual retreat.

437
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:38,720
I have to go solo and bring my son…

438
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,080
to the event.

439
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:44,440
Oh, and where will he change?

440
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:47,560
Oh, I've prepared a room upstairs.

441
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:50,080
There's a special spot for you,
Mr. Pun, and…

442
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:54,440
This is my wife, Pie.

443
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:56,960
Nice to meet you, Ms. Pie.

444
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:59,240
Beautiful skin and such a great figure.

445
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:00,840
You're absolutely sweet.

446
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:03,080
You'll look amazing
in the outfit I've prepared.

447
00:32:03,680 --> 00:32:05,480
It's going to turn out perfect.

448
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:10,120
Don't expect too much, okay?

449
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,560
Everyone's new here.

450
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:13,880
If anything goes wrong,
you'll be disappointed.

451
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,120
Mom.

452
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:20,160
Aunt Nhun, Pun, James.

453
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,600
- Hello!
- Oh, Mink!

454
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,720
- Hello!
- Hello, Uncle Dech.

455
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:27,360
- Hi, James.
- Mink, oh my God!

456
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:30,720
I've missed you so much.
You're so gorgeous.

457
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:34,720
Look at you, all dressed up,
hair and makeup done.

458
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:38,080
Just change your outfit
and we're good to go for the shoot.

459
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,920
She's the real deal.

460
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:42,120
You won't be disappointed.

461
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,840
James, go all out!

462
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,120
Alright.

463
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:48,480
Let's head upstairs now.

464
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:51,000
- Okay. Mink, let's go!
- Let's go!

465
00:32:56,520 --> 00:32:59,320
Pie, see? It's going to be fun.

466
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:02,640
I promise you won't get bored.

467
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:06,480
Come on. Smile.

468
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:09,360
Okay.

469
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:10,280
Let's go.

470
00:34:34,600 --> 00:34:37,440
- Are you okay?
- Sorry.

471
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:38,600
- Does it hurt anywhere?
- Oh no.

472
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,520
I'm fine.

473
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:41,960
What on earth are you doing?

474
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:43,320
Look at this.

475
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:45,440
Everything's spilled everywhere.

476
00:34:45,520 --> 00:34:47,440
And your outfit's ruined too.

477
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,239
You're so embarrassing.

478
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:53,960
Sorry, I got lightheaded and dizzy.

479
00:34:54,040 --> 00:34:56,159
That's why this happened. I'm sorry.

480
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:57,400
Alright.

481
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:59,800
I'll go apologize to the host.

482
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:02,160
As for you, do whatever you need to,

483
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:04,240
but don't embarrass me again.

484
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:43,840
Can't take it. Don't want to stay.

485
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:45,320
You want to go home, right?

486
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,560
Don't make that face.

487
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:54,960
I know. If it were me,
I wouldn't want to stay either.

488
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:02,680
If you want to leave, I can help.

489
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:09,120
Do you want me to?

490
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:22,880
What happened?

491
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,760
Oh no.

492
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,600
What happened here?

493
00:36:29,680 --> 00:36:32,360
Pie fainted and fell onto the table.

494
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:47,120
- Pie!
- Hey, Pie!

495
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,560
- Pie!
- Don't crowd around.

496
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,360
- Pie!
- Does anyone have an inhaler?

497
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,240
Pun, let's take her outside.

498
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:56,080
The air out there is fresher.

499
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:58,520
- Let's do that. I'll help.
- Okay.

500
00:36:58,600 --> 00:36:59,520
Come on.

501
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,560
‪Alright.

502
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:05,640
Pie! It's okay. I'll carry her.

503
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:07,880
Pie!

504
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:21,400
James.

505
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:24,880
I think we should cut Pie out,
since she won't be able to continue.

506
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:27,240
But I'm supposed to shoot with Pie, right?

507
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:30,440
With her falling and passing out,
it's not going to work.

508
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,560
Let her go home.

509
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:35,480
If we shoot and have to stop halfway,
it will be a waste of time.

510
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:37,000
It's better for her to go home.

511
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:39,240
If she leaves, then I'll leave too.

512
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,720
Mr. Pun, please calm down first.

513
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:47,080
Exactly. I promised him I'd do this,
so I have to keep my word.

514
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,880
Your wife has a reason to back out,

515
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:52,280
but you're fine.
You can't just back out like that.

516
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:55,160
Stay and help James for now, please.

517
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:57,320
Think of it as doing it for my sake, okay?

518
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:00,000
The set is ready now.

519
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:02,320
We need to start shooting soon,

520
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:05,520
or we'll run out of time on the location.

521
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,400
Mr. Pun, could you help me out?

522
00:38:07,480 --> 00:38:11,360
As for Pie, I'll have my assistant
take good care of her.

523
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:14,280
He's going to get an inhaler
for her right now.

524
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:16,440
Could you help me just a little?

525
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:17,760
Please, Pun.

526
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:27,120
Alright, I'll do it. But…

527
00:38:27,720 --> 00:38:29,760
please make sure
Pie is taken care of properly.

528
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:32,120
As for the photoshoot,

529
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:35,800
I'll call my sister to come pick her up
so she can rest at home.

530
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,960
Once I'm done with the call,
I'll rush to the set,

531
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:39,280
so we can continue shooting.

532
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:41,000
- Thank you so much.
- Okay.

533
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:43,120
Then let's find someone
to do the shoot with Pun.

534
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:45,800
About the damages, don't worry, James.

535
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,280
I'll take care of everything.

536
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:49,680
I'll have the dirty clothes
dry-cleaned and sent back.

537
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:50,960
Pie.

538
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:52,880
Pie.

539
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:58,680
Pun.

540
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:00,080
Hey.

541
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:03,560
You don't have to do the photoshoot today.

542
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:05,440
I'll call Rok

543
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:09,240
to pick you up,
so you can rest at home, okay?

544
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:12,400
Okay, Pun.

545
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:17,400
Wait here. I'll go call Rok first.

546
00:39:18,840 --> 00:39:20,280
Thank you.

547
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:12,360
<i>Hello. Little Krarok can't answer</i>
<i>the phone right now.</i>

548
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:14,800
<i>Feel free to leave a message!</i>

549
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:27,760
Hey, Koh. I need your help with something.

550
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:55,040
You fainted from hunger?

551
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:02,920
Calm down.

552
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:05,600
Pun sent me to take you home.

553
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:07,840
Don't be so shocked.

554
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:11,360
Krarok didn't answer his call,
so I came instead.

555
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:13,680
Let's go. My car is over there.

556
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,360
I'm not going.

557
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:19,480
I can go home myself.

558
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:24,000
But Pun sent me to pick you up.

559
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:26,920
If you don't come with me,
I'll have to call him.

560
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:31,200
You'd better come up
with a good reason to explain to him

561
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:32,560
why you're not going with me.

562
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:42,560
- Wow, beautiful!
- Yeah.

563
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,080
- Look at that.
- That's great.

564
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:45,240
Her skin is so nice.

565
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:47,960
She got her skin from me. Look at me.

566
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:48,960
- Yeah, sure.
- So fair.

567
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:50,360
- She looks amazing!
- Yeah.

568
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:52,400
Look at her pose.

569
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:54,120
Posing so beautifully.

570
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:56,360
She's posing so perfectly.

571
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:58,680
Has she worked
as a professional model before?

572
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:01,400
Oh no, not at all, James.

573
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:06,480
She's done a few small modeling gigs,
but not professionally.

574
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:09,520
You can't say she's not professional

575
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,640
because she studied fashion.

576
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:15,760
She must have some experience
to be this good, right?

577
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,440
Yeah, I agree.

578
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:21,400
Without experience,
no way she could pose like that.

579
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:24,320
I'm sure this shoot
is going to turn out great.

580
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:25,920
- Really?
- I'm feeling more at ease now.

581
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:28,400
- Awesome.
- If you're at ease, then I am too.

582
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:08,720
Why are you stopping?

583
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:11,440
I'm stopping for food.

584
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:13,400
You're starving, aren't you?

585
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:15,880
I'm not eating.

586
00:43:17,920 --> 00:43:19,320
If you don't eat now,

587
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:22,120
I checked the map, and there's traffic.

588
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:24,040
It'll take around 90 minutes to get home.

589
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:29,080
I'm not eating. I can wait.

590
00:43:41,360 --> 00:43:43,680
Looks like your stomach can't wait.

591
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:48,960
I'll go grab something for you real quick.

592
00:43:57,200 --> 00:43:58,920
- Hello.
- Hi there!

593
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:01,280
How many would you like today, handsome?

594
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:03,440
- Ten, please.
- Huh?

595
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:05,080
I can't eat that much. Just one, please.

596
00:45:10,680 --> 00:45:13,040
- Not eating?
- No.

597
00:45:27,360 --> 00:45:28,560
I'm not eating.

598
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:33,360
Suit yourself.

599
00:45:48,280 --> 00:45:49,360
Fine, I'll eat.

600
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:51,560
I'll finish it all,

601
00:45:51,640 --> 00:45:54,200
so I don't have to keep smelling
the grilled chicken.

602
00:45:58,400 --> 00:45:59,360
Okay.

603
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:01,720
That's a good reason.

604
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:21,960
Go ahead. Enjoy.

605
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:56,520
Okay, great! Looks good.

606
00:46:58,400 --> 00:46:59,920
A little closer, please.

607
00:47:04,720 --> 00:47:08,360
Now, turn to face each other,
and look into each other's eyes.

608
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:13,560
Closer, please.

609
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:16,520
Just a little more.

610
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:20,520
Perfect.

611
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:25,400
Look at that.

612
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:27,760
The more I see, the more I regret it.

613
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:30,960
Hey, let it go.

614
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:33,640
You already have a daughter-in-law.

615
00:47:33,720 --> 00:47:35,320
Let's talk about it in the next life.

616
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:37,360
No, this life!

617
00:47:37,440 --> 00:47:39,760
What do you mean next life? Look.

618
00:47:39,840 --> 00:47:41,880
Excellent. That looks amazing!

619
00:49:31,720 --> 00:49:33,280
Just here a little.

620
00:49:33,840 --> 00:49:35,840
Hold it. Yes, just like that.

621
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:25,560
Pie.

622
00:50:32,960 --> 00:50:33,960
Pie.

623
00:50:37,920 --> 00:50:38,880
Pie.

624
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:26,800
Thanks for driving me home.

625
00:51:36,080 --> 00:51:37,520
I'm sorry if my mom

626
00:51:38,680 --> 00:51:41,480
said anything rude when she came
to see you the other day.

627
00:51:43,160 --> 00:51:44,480
I told her not to do that again.

628
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:41,040
That was beautiful.
I'm really glad about today.

629
00:52:42,080 --> 00:52:43,000
Great job!

630
00:52:43,080 --> 00:52:45,320
- Excellent work! Thank you so much.
- You did great.

631
00:52:45,400 --> 00:52:48,080
- Thank you.
- Both of you did an amazing job.

632
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:50,200
Let's take a look
at the results over here.

633
00:52:51,560 --> 00:52:54,000
Pun, want to take a selfie?

634
00:52:54,920 --> 00:52:57,800
Today was so much fun.
I'd love to keep a picture as a memory.

635
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:01,880
Mink, after taking pictures
together all day,

636
00:53:01,960 --> 00:53:03,160
you still want more?

637
00:53:03,240 --> 00:53:05,360
With you, never enough.

638
00:53:08,200 --> 00:53:10,120
I mean the pictures.

639
00:53:11,440 --> 00:53:12,440
Come on.

640
00:53:31,200 --> 00:53:32,120
NEW POST

641
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,360
<i>"My partner in crime.</i>

642
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:37,200
<i>It was so much fun working today.</i>

643
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:39,520
<i>Thanks so much to Pun, Aunt Nhun,</i>

644
00:53:39,600 --> 00:53:41,800
<i>and James for being so kind to me.</i>

645
00:53:42,400 --> 00:53:45,000
<i>Thanks for having me today.</i>
<i>It was a lot of fun."</i>

646
00:54:06,440 --> 00:54:12,240
PUN PARIT LIKED YOUR PHOTO

647
00:54:55,560 --> 00:54:58,440
Pie, look at the photo Mink posted!

648
00:55:01,520 --> 00:55:04,240
Hey, don't you feel anything about this?

649
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:06,800
She wrote "My partner in crime," you know?

650
00:55:06,880 --> 00:55:09,040
Only couples write stuff like that!

651
00:55:09,120 --> 00:55:11,400
It's fine. Let her do whatever she wants.

652
00:55:11,480 --> 00:55:14,480
Wait, are you seriously not jealous?

653
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:18,200
What's the point of being jealous?

654
00:55:18,280 --> 00:55:20,080
Hey, Pie. No way!

655
00:55:20,160 --> 00:55:22,680
You have to be jealous, Pie!
Jealous, you know?

656
00:55:23,520 --> 00:55:25,480
If it were me, I wouldn't let it go.

657
00:55:25,560 --> 00:55:27,480
Nobody touches my man!

658
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:31,880
Seriously, Rok.

659
00:55:35,680 --> 00:55:37,800
He might be a better match
for her than for me.

660
00:55:39,400 --> 00:55:42,560
With her family background,
manners, everything.

661
00:55:44,600 --> 00:55:47,240
At this point, if Pun really chooses Mink…

662
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:51,480
I'll accept it.

663
00:55:53,760 --> 00:55:54,920
Wait.

664
00:55:57,880 --> 00:56:00,600
No way, Pie. You can't think like that.

665
00:56:01,920 --> 00:56:03,680
Don't give up yet.

666
00:56:04,440 --> 00:56:08,240
Is there something going on
between you and him?

667
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:13,120
Well.

668
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:16,920
It's just typical couple stuff.
Nothing to worry about.

669
00:56:18,040 --> 00:56:21,240
Honestly, being single,
like you, isn't so bad.

670
00:56:33,120 --> 00:56:34,200
Pun…

671
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:47,640
You know, right?

672
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:49,680
Mink likes you.

673
00:56:49,760 --> 00:56:50,880
Yeah.

674
00:56:50,960 --> 00:56:53,840
When you look at Pie,
it's not like she's your brother's wife.

675
00:56:53,920 --> 00:56:55,800
What are you trying to stir up with me?

676
00:56:56,480 --> 00:56:59,640
Ask yourself how you look
at someone's husband.

677
00:56:59,720 --> 00:57:02,720
<i>Someone smart like you should know,</i>

678
00:57:02,800 --> 00:57:06,280
you don't fit into Pun's family,
yet you're still trying to stick around.

679
00:57:06,360 --> 00:57:08,680
If it were me,
I would've left a long time ago.

680
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:11,360
I got an appointment with Dr. Bee.

681
00:57:11,440 --> 00:57:13,800
We're talking about IVF tomorrow.

682
00:57:13,880 --> 00:57:16,000
Have you ever been pregnant
or had a miscarriage?

683
00:57:17,320 --> 00:57:20,320
<i>Photos might not tell the full story.</i>

684
00:57:21,080 --> 00:57:23,080
<i>I think it's best if you see for yourself.</i>

685
00:57:23,920 --> 00:57:26,280
Dad, I don't know
how long you've been deceiving us.

686
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:28,840
But today, you have to choose.
Make a decision.

687
00:57:55,880 --> 00:57:58,800
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
